Key Signature Description type <code>string</code> Type of parameter, possible values: <code>"string"\|"number"\|"boolean"</code> name <code>string</code> Parameter name default <code>string\|number\|boolean\|nil</code> Default value <p>Component example:</p> <pre><code>component.register({
    id = "component1",
    name = "Test component 1",
    description = "The test component 1",
    params = {
        message = { type = "string", name = "Message", default = "Hello world!" }
    },
    start = function(params)
        message = params.message
        return coroutine.create(function()
            while true do
                print(message)
                coroutine.yield(1000)
            end
        end)
    end
})
</code></pre> <p>Created coroutine in <code>start</code> function may have infinity loop, but must be in it placed calling <code>coroutine.yield</code>. Paramter of <code>coroutine.yield</code> is optional number, which mean number of miliseconds wich coroutine is ommited from resumining. No need to worry about started coroutine terminating, is terminated during script VM reloading or when user change component parameter values.</p> <p>This will looks like in web interface:</p> <p></p>
